This project focuses on designing and developing a basic website to demonstrate foundational web design skills. It uses core web technologies such as HTML for structuring content and CSS for styling and layout. The website is designed with a clean and simple user interface, ensuring ease of navigation and readability.

The project emphasizes essential design principles, including proper page structure, consistent styling, and responsive layouts for different screen sizes. It also highlights the use of semantic HTML, basic visual hierarchy, and organized code to improve maintainability and user experience.

This website serves as a beginner-friendly project aimed at understanding how web pages are built and styled from scratch. It is suitable for learning the fundamentals of web development and acts as a strong starting point for more advanced projects involving interactivity, frameworks, or backend integration.
